      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tech 2010</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Fuchs letter on June 11 special issue on millennium's social issues hopes bots will not be used to haggle over price of soft drinks at McDonald's0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I'm hardly a Luddite (I've been a Web developer since 1994 and a technophile for much longer), but David Brooks's description, in his essay ''The Mall,'' of using a personal digital assistant to haggle at McDonald's over an 89-cent soft drink, sounds like my idea of hell. If the bot can negotiate a lower price, fine; but what I really want is not to have to worry about such things. I'm hopeful that the people designing these devices will be aware of this.</p>
        <p>Michael Fuchs</p>
        <p>Palo Alto, Calif.</p>
      </block>
